name: market for tomato seedling, for planting | tomato seedling, for planting | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/15222/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for  'tomato seedling, for planting', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;The product 'tomato seedling, for planting' represents 1 tomato seedling. It is an annual crop. This product is used for plant propagation. A seedling is a young plant raised from seed in a nursery. The seedlings are produced in a greenhouse (heated or unheated). 

This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce 'tomato seedling, for planting',  within the geography of Global.

This activity ends with the supply of 'tomato seedling, for planting',  to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.

Estimated value. The transport has been calculated as the weighted average of the seedling transport for the activities: 

tomato production, fresh grade, in heated greenhouse, NL, PV = 8.25E+08kg, seedling input 5.80E-02kg, transport “transport, freight, lorry >32 metric ton, EURO4” of 0.00029tkm, comment: Seedling transport from seedling farm (Netherlands) to tomato farm (Netherlands)Distance: 50 km (assumption)Weight = 100 g / seedling with moisture and container (Stoessel et al. 2012)

tomato production, fresh grade, in unheated greenhouse, ES, PV = 4.26E+09kg, seedling input 1.70E-01kg, transport “transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO4” of 0.00089tkm, comment: Supply of bed and substrate from processing plant to tomato farmBed and substrate lifespan: 3 yearsDefault assumption for distance 300 km

tomato production, fresh grade, open field, MX, PV = 2.89E+09kg, seedling input 7.56E-01kg, transport “transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO4” of 0.0046tkm, comment: Seedling transport from seedling farm (Mexico) to tomato farm (Mexico) (Seedlings are procuded in the same country of the tomato (Stoessel et al. 2012)2.8 seedlings/m2 (Martinez-Blanco et al. 2011)Distance: 50 km (assumption)Weight = 100 g / seedling with moisture and container (Stoessel et al. 2012)
